article.headline: Hofstra 87, James Madison 66
article.story: HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. (AP) -- Aurimas Keiza was 8-for-11 from the field and had a career-high 24 points as Hofstra won its fifth straight overall and 12th in a row at home, 87-66 over James Madison on Thursday night. Freshman Mike Davis-Sabb, making his first collegiate start, had 16 points on 6-of-7 seven shooting, six rebounds and four assists, while Antoine Agudio had 16 points for the Pride (9-2, 2-1 Colonial Athletic Association). Davis-Sabb, whose previous high this season was three points, started in place of center Adrian Uter who suffered a minor injury in warmups and didn't play. Juwann James and Jomo Belfor each had 16 points for the Dukes (3-8, 0-3), who lost their third straight. Carlos Rivera had five of his 12 points as Hofstra opened the game on a 16-2 run. James Madison got within 20-15 on two free throws by Belfor with 9:36 left in the half, but Hofstra went on to a 40-28 halftime lead. The biggest lead was 75-49 on a free throw by Davis-Sabb with 8:50 to go.
